ZCZC GE63
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
SUNDAY EVENING A LOW 995 CENTRED 52 N 26 W MOVS SLWY E AND DEEPENS TO BE
984 55 N 21 W BY MIDDAY MONDAY. THIS LOW THEN LOSES ITS IDENTITY OVERNIGHT
INTO TUESDAY. ALSO SUNDAY EVENING A HIGH 1024 IS CENTRED OVER ICELAND. THIS
HIGH REMAINS INSITU UNTIL LATE MONDAY WHEN IT MOVS AWAY NWARDS. MIDDAY TUESDAY
A NEW LOW 976 CENTRED 57 N 25 W MOVS EWARDS AND DEEPENS TO BE 972 HEBRIDES
BY MIDDAY WEDNESDAY. STRG WINDS DEVELOP IN FORTIES CROMARTY AND FAIR ISLE
EARLY ON TUESDAY MORNING WITH POSS GALES IN FAIR ISLE BY MIDDAY TUESDAY.
LATER ON TUESDAY THE STRG WINDS EASE ACROSS FORTIES AND CROMARTY BUT ARE
LIKELY TO CONTINUE IN FAIR ISLE WITH POSS GALES THROUGH WEDNESDAY WITH MORE
WIDESPREAD GALES LIKELY IN FAIR ISLE LATER ON WEDNESDAY. DURING WEDNESDAY
MORNING STRG WINDS DEVELOP IN THE N SEA S OF 56 N.
